  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check + FR-2.3</step>
    <step order="1">Implement `ScheduledJobRegistry` (in-memory dict of jobId → IScheduledJob)</step>
    <step order="2">Implement `ScheduledJobHost.StartAsync`: load Dataverse rows + Cronos cron parsing + per-job PeriodicTimer</step>
    <step order="3">Implement dispatch path: build JobRunContext + invoke ExecuteAsync + write sprk_backgroundjobrun + capture failure</step>
    <step order="4">Implement hourly refresh of Dataverse job rows (catches new/disabled/changed jobs)</step>
    <step order="5">Honor cancellation throughout (per NFR-07)</step>
    <step order="6">Unit tests: cron parsing, dispatch invocation, run-record write, cancellation propagation</step>
    <step order="7">Build + tests + publish-size</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Cronos cron expressions parse correctly (e.g., `0 2 * * *`)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Job dispatched on schedule → IScheduledJob.ExecuteAsync invoked → run row written</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Cancellation propagates to in-flight jobs within 30s</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Hourly Dataverse refresh picks up new/changed/disabled jobs</criterion>
